refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.changelog;
&Version; &Description;
7.1.0
As of PHP 7.1.0, a dedicated output buffer is used, url_rewriter.tags is used solely for output functions and url_rewriter.hosts is available. Prior to PHP 7.1.0, rewrite variables set by output_add_rewrite_var shared an output buffer with transparent session id support (see session.trans_sid_tags).

  &reftitle.examples;



    output_add_rewrite_var example


<?php
ini_set('url_rewriter.tags', 'a=href,form=');

output_add_rewrite_var('var', 'value');

// some links
echo '<a href="file.php">link</a>
<a href="http://example.com">link2</a>';

// a form
echo '<form action="script.php" method="post">
<input type="text" name="var2" />
</form>';

print_r(ob_list_handlers());
?>


    &example.outputs;


<a href="file.php?var=value">link</a>
<a href="http://example.com">link2</a>

<form action="script.php" method="post">
<input type="hidden" name="var" value="value" />
<input type="text" name="var2" />
</form>

Array
(
    [0] => URL-Rewriter
)
